Remaining Steps
IMPORTANT:
    In the FLOW Section: if integration is big then the right side gets trimmed, also in PDF only the default View of Flow gets captured, how to deal with it in PDF?

Step 18 — Navigation / View routing
- Right now everything is in one flat view. As the app grows we need a proper way to move between Upload → Results → (future views). Simple state-based routing inside Zustand — no React Router needed yet.

Step 19 — Analysis panel
- A dedicated section that auto-generates observations from the parsed metadata. Things like:
    - "This integration has no fault handlers on invoke connections — risk of unhandled errors"
    - "BASIC_AUTH detected on outbound connection — consider OAuth"
    - "Only 1 tracking variable set as primary"
Pure logic, no AI needed. Rule-based analysis from the metadata shape.

Step 20 — Multi-file / history
- Allow uploading multiple .iar files in a session and switching between them. Store parsed results in a list in Zustand. Useful for comparing integrations.

Step 21 — Backend scaffold
- Move parsers and generators to an Express or FastAPI backend. Frontend stays identical — just swap fetch calls. This unlocks larger file handling, server-side PDF generation, and eventually a database for saving docs.

Step 22 — Export improvements
- PDF cover page with logo/branding
- Word document (.docx) export
- Copy-to-clipboard for individual sections